.TH "rpcrdma_bc_receive_call" 9 "rpcrdma_bc_receive_call" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rpcrdma_bc_receive_call \- Handle a reverse-direction Call
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" rpcrdma_bc_receive_call
.BI "(struct rpcrdma_xprt *r_xprt "  ","
.BI "struct rpcrdma_rep *rep "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "r_xprt" 12
transport receiving the call
.IP "rep" 12
receive buffer containing the call
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Operational assumptions:
o Backchannel credits are ignored, just as the NFS server
forechannel currently does
o The ULP manages a replay cache (eg, NFSv4.1 sessions).
No replay detection is done at the transport level
